Here is a re-factor.

```java
class Point {
    double x, y;

    Point(double x, double y) {
        this.x = x;
        this.y = y;
    }

    static String slope(Point a, Point b) {
        double m = (b.y - a.y) / (b.x - a.x);
        return &quot;m = (%s - %s) / (%s - %s) = %s&quot;.formatted(b.y, a.y, b.x, a.x, m);
    }
}
```

Output

```none
m = (8.0 - 2.0) / (13.0 - 1.0) = 0.5
```

Alternately, use a _[record class](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/21/language/records.html)_.

```java
record Point(double x, double y) {
    static String slope(Point a, Point b) {
        double m = (b.y - a.y) / (b.x - a.x);
        return &quot;m = (%s - %s) / (%s - %s) = %s&quot;.formatted(b.y, a.y, b.x, a.x, m);
    }
}
```

